  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes a single variation axis in an OpenType variable font.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationAxis` describes a single variation axis defined in an OpenType
variable font. It exposes the axis tag, its allowed range, default value, and
whether the axis is hidden from end-user interfaces.

Obtain instances via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.VariationDesignParameters> or
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.GetVariationDesignParameters*>. Use the information
to build <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate> values when cloning
a typeface with custom variation settings.

This is a value type; no disposal is required.

## Examples

```csharp
// Enumerate variation axes of a typeface
SKFontVariationAxis[] axes = typeface.VariationDesignParameters;
foreach (var axis in axes)
{
    Console.WriteLine(
        $"{axis.Tag}: min={axis.Min}, default={axis.Default}, max={axis.Max}, hidden={axis.IsHidden}");
}
```
]]></format></remarks>
